	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello all!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
    i don't play EQ, but i like roleplaying games and have been looking for one i can get envolved with. from what i have read and from what i have heard form others this is a great game. i did have some trouble locating people who liked to rp so i was reluctant to buy this game. a friend pointed out everlore and thanx to them i have found you guys.i played D&amp;D (dungeons and dragons) for some years now and have learned a few tricks to making and keeping a good character. so with the respect you deserve i am humbally submitting my own ideas... i am sorry for my spelling, i read all the time and still can't spell worth a darn!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Tips... <BR>
<BR>
1) histories are one of the most impotant things to mold before embarking on rpg adventures. give them texture, make them realistic (fantasy... realistic? ironic huh?). make your character interact with the world around him... he is in Norrath so don't say he is from Avalon. second part of tip one, be origanal... none of this &quot;my parents were slaughtered by a dragon&quot; stuff (i in no way mean to be offensive to those that have used that background, infact i incourage you to use it... it makes it more common and even more of a reason for others to discard it). if your gonna come up with a back ground do something that is gonna give your character weaknesses and strengths... &quot;i was found in the ruins of a large demolished ship afloat in the ocean (what ever ocean you choose) and beacuse of that i have had a deep rooted fear of water and all the uglies that swim in it&quot; or how about this... &quot;i am very superstisious. i won't walk on a grave, cross a stream, or converse with necromancers&quot; the possablilites are endless. weaknesses are a strength in your personality &quot;yes i have these flaws but i over came them and now have a stronger sense of self-esteem than those that had no fear to begain with&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
2) items are impotant too... if your character likes the color green... get green stuff. dark elves might like dark blue to black colors... or even better a dark elf with an eye for the bright and flashy... be unique thats whats gonna make EQ flavorful ;)<BR>
<BR>
3) HATE FOR ANOTHER RACE. now thats fun to play! &quot;i hate halflings! whats worse than a bunch of fuzzy footed, curly haired, ankle biters!? we Dark Elves should band together and wipe those freaks off the face of Norrath!&quot;... &quot; Dark Elves!? HAHA! whats worse than being one? a bile Golam has a better smell! mysterious!? they rant and rave about themselves all the time! whats so secret about them? we all know the truth! Dark Elves are nothing but Veeshan's toe jam!&quot; (i like these two races so don't be offended, its role playing not the truth).<BR>
<BR>
3) study unique skills! nothing is better than being able to say &quot;oh i can do that! Here let me help you!&quot; (&quot;for a price&quot; if your character is greedy).<BR>
<BR>
4) if your an Ogre talk like one! hotkey a burp once in a while. if your a gnome... be curious, &quot;everything has a law that can be broken!&quot;. If your a wood elf be nice and always perfer the woods over the city, &quot;Nah, i perfer to camp outside tonight&quot; (unless your background prevents this behavior, who says wood elves wern't raised by city folk?).<BR>
<BR>
5) Above all have fun, its a role playing GAME! just play for enjoyment! your not racing anybody (unless thats fun to you and if it is go for it!)... slow down and not only level up your stats but let your character's personality grow!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
these are a small and modest group of tips... i didn't give more because its your character not mine... be unique and create what you want to play... i just know that fresh ideas help out sometimes... have fun and i hope i see you guys on a role playing surver in the future :)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
